The error execute only when us put a DefaultCommand to Tank Subystem in the RobotContainer.

On line 10 of your DriveCommand, you are creating a second TankSubsystem. That will cause the error you are seeing. You just need to declare it there and then assign the TankSubsystem as you already are on line 17 (this is the one from RobotContainer, which is the one you want).

Also, you no longer need Robot.java line 38. The command will do that now.

The next time you have an error like this, please include the Java stack trace that you will find after the message mentioning StartCompetition. If you take a close look at the stack trace, you should see that line 10 in DriveCommand is where things went wrong.
